gwiz2 was built against Qt 4.8.

To build, run

qmake

Then run,

make


Setup...

In your linuxcnc.ini file, add gwiz2 config (change as appropriate)

[GWIZARD]
WizardDirs = "/home/frankt/linuxcnc-dev/ikfast/contrib/gwiz2/wizards/lathe_wizards;/home/frankt/linuxcnc-dev/ikfast/contrib/gwiz2/wizards/general_wizards"  ; Where the gwiz2 wizards live.  Semi-colon separated list
WizFileDir = "/home/frankt/linux-cnc/wiz_files"  ; Directory to store user created .wiz files.
GWiz2IniFilePath = "/home/frankt/linuxcnc-dev/ikfast/contrib/gwiz2/gwiz2.ini" ; GWiz2 static settings


And add to the FILTER section (again, change paths)...

[FILTER]
PROGRAM_EXTENSION = .wiz GWiz Wizard File
wiz = /home/frankt/linuxcnc-dev/ikfast/contrib/gwiz2/wiz2gcode


To run gwiz, either...

gwiz2 -ini <path to linuxcnc.ini> <optional wiz file to edit>


OR, add ini file path to .bashrc...

export INI_FILE_NAME=<path to linuxcnc.ini>

and then run...

gwiz2 <optional wiz file to edit>


